Rating: 2
It kind of had a matzah ball taste to it. Much better taste and texture than store bought passover pasta. I just steamed some fresh veggies and tossed on some shredded mozzarella. With limited food options on Passover, I would definitely make this again, though it will never compete with the real thing.

Rating: 2
Not bad considering it's made from matzo meal, but certainly no substitute for the real thing. I used whatever fresh green veggies I could find (asparagus, green pepper, artichoke, scallions) so at least they were delicious.